[2] Monitoring on farms: comment
Date: 7 Mar 2014
From: Nick Honhold <nick.honhold@gmail.com> [edited]

Re: Avian influenza (36): China, LPAI H7N9, poultry, monitoring, RFI
-----------------------------------------------------
I looked at the Veterinary Bureau report on-line using the link in the [above] Promed post. The translation [from Chinese] (by Google) shows at least the provinces sampled and also that all 64 sero-positive samples were from Hunan. The 2 virus positive samples were also from Hunan.

Of the 32 Provinces listed in the report, serum samples were tested from 9 and pathogen testing was done in 10, with 7 provinces having both types of sampling and 20 had neither.

No information on the numbers of samples from different production systems overall or by province.

--
Communicated by:
Nick Honhold
Independent veterinary Epidemiologist
<nick.honhold@gmail.com>

